# DresOS microG: sepolicy.rule
#
# The Zygisk signature spoof companion runs in the magisk domain. It only
# reads the bundled Google certificate from the module directory, which
# the magisk domain can already access by default on stock Magisk. This
# rule is a defensive belt for hardened forks where the magisk domain has
# been narrowed. It is intentionally minimal.

allow magisk system_file file { read getattr open }
